.TH MODE_T 3 2021-11-02 Linux "Linux Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
mode_t \- file attributes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <sys/types.h>
.PP
.BR typedef " /* ... */ " mode_t;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Used for some file attributes (e.g., file mode).
According to POSIX,
it shall be an integer type.
.SH CONFORMING TO
POSIX.1-2001 and later.
.SH NOTES
The following headers also provide this type:
.IR <fcntl.h> ,
.IR <ndbm.h> ,
.IR <spawn.h> ,
.IR <sys/ipc.h> ,
.IR <sys/mman.h> ,
and
.IR <sys/stat.h> .
.PP
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chmod (2),
.BR mkdir (2),
.BR open (2),
.BR umask (2),
.BR stat-struct (3)
